# BPMN domain

## Element kinds

`startEvent`, `endEvent`, `userTask`, `scriptTask`, `exclusiveGateway`, `parallelGateway`, `inclusiveGateway`, `subProcess`

## Gateways

| Type | Fork | Join |
|------|------|------|
| exclusive | first matching condition; optional `isDefault` | — |
| parallel | all outgoing | wait all incoming |
| inclusive | all matching | same as parallel on join |

Join token state → `ProcessInstance.InternalState` (not API-visible).

## Conditions (`EvalCondition`)

- **Sequence flows** at gateways only — NOT on linear start→next edges
- Operators: `==`, `!=`, `>=`, `>`, `<=`, `<`, bare truthy field
- Left-hand side supports dot paths: `order.amount >= 100`, `item.kk == 11`
- Missing path: `==`/numeric → false; `!=` → true

## startEvent (`eventDefinition`) — BPMN 2.0

Schema: `schemas/process-definition.schema.json`, trigger: `schemas/trigger-message.schema.json`

| type | BPMN 2.0 | JSON fields | Trigger |
|------|----------|-------------|---------|
| `none` | None start | (omit) | `POST /process-instances` |
| `message` | messageEventDefinition | `messageRef`, `condition?`, `correlationKey?` | `POST /triggers/message` |
| `conditional` | conditionalEventDefinition | `condition` | external + condition eval |
| `signal` | signalEventDefinition | `signalRef` | future `/triggers/signal` |
| `timer` | timerEventDefinition | `timerCycle` | external scheduler |

Airtable / webhook pattern: Adapter normalizes payload → `POST /api/v1/triggers/message` with matching `messageRef`.

## userTask fields

- `assignees`: approver list
- `approvalMode`: `any` | `all` | `sequential` (aliases: 或签, 会签, 顺签)
- `requiredApprovals`: for `any` mode, GitHub-style quota from assignee pool (default **1**)
- `returnTo`: element id to re-activate on reject (default: upstream userTask)
- `onReject`: `return` (default) | `terminateScope`
- `scopeId`: sub-process scope for parallel regions
- `autoComplete`: skip wait (tests)
- Complete API: `assignee`, `action` (approve|reject), `comment`, `variables`

Partial completion persists `pending_assignees` and `approval_records` on the activity until the node finishes.

## subProcess

Marker element: `scopeId`, `entryRef`, `exitRef`. Elements with matching `scopeId` belong to the scope.

- **Reject (`onReject: return`)**: re-activate `returnTo` (or default upstream userTask); only cancels same parallel branch (`branch_flow_id`); clears join tokens in scope.
- **Terminate scope**: `POST .../terminate` with `{ "scopeId": "..." }` → cancels active activities in scope, instance stays `running` if work remains outside scope.
- **Terminate instance**: `POST .../terminate` without `scopeId` → `status: cancelled`.

## Runtime APIs

- `POST /api/v1/assignee-sync/remove-user` — canonical personnel sync (adapter target)
- `POST /api/v1/assignee-sync/replace`
- `PATCH /api/v1/process-instances/{id}/tasks/{activityId}/assignees`
- `POST /api/v1/process-instances/{id}/terminate`
- `POST /api/v1/triggers/message` — message start (Airtable/webhook adapters)

## Event plugins

See [docs/plugins.md](../../docs/plugins.md).

| Env | Role |
|-----|------|
| `EVENT_CONSUMER` | `memory` \| `redis` \| `kafka` \| `nats` \| `rabbitmq` \| `none` |
| `PLUGIN_ASSIGNEE_ADAPTERS` | Assignee stream (HR sync) |
| `PLUGIN_TRIGGER_ADAPTERS` | Trigger stream (process start) |
| `PLUGIN_TASK_ADAPTERS` | Task stream (approve / reject) |
| `PLUGIN_CONTROL_ADAPTERS` | Control stream (terminate) |
| `PLUGIN_WASM_DIR` | WASM + capability sandbox |

Ingress: `POST /api/v1/events/assignee/{source}`, `/trigger/{source}`, `/task/{source}`, `/control/{source}`.

Activity fields: `scope_id`, `branch_flow_id`, `outcome` (`approve`|`reject`|`cancelled`).
